\"transit advocates\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 397}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 414, \"to\": 424}, {\"ngram\": \"cities\", \"from\": 428, \"to\": 434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris hasclosed more than 100 streetsto motor vehicles,tripled parking feesfor SUVs, removed roughly 50,000 parking spots, and constructed more than 1,300 kilometers (800 miles) of bike lanes since Mayor Anne Hidalgo took office in 2014.\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 447, \"end\": 452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999708507, \"rank\": 2.9157430667192093e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 651, \"end\": 663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than 100 streetsto motor vehicles\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"parking\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 517}, {\"ngram\": \"SUVs\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"roughly 50,000 parking spots\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 568}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 1,300 kilometers\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"800 miles\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 623}, {\"ngram\": \"bike lanes\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 638}, {\"ngram\": \"office\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 675}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those changes have contributed to a40% decline in air pollution, according to city officials.\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 779, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Those changes\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 699}, {\"ngram\": \"a40% decline\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 732}, {\"ngram\": \"air pollution\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 749}, {\"ngram\": \"city officials\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 778}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"How did we achieve this?\\\"\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 807, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hidalgo saidin a statementin March.\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 843, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hidalgo\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 815}, {\"ngram\": \"a statementin March\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 842}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"By assuming a major and radical rupture: the end of car-dependence.\\\"\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 913, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a major and radical rupture\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"car-dependence\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris and other European cities have for years been at the forefront of efforts to reduce car use, though their successeshave not come without challenges.\", \"from\": 915, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 915, \"end\": 920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999708507, \"rank\": 2.9157430667192093e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other European cities\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 946}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 961}, {\"ngram\": \"the forefront\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 983}, {\"ngram\": \"efforts\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 994}, {\"ngram\": \"car use\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1012}, {\"ngram\": \"their successeshave\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"challenges\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1068}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S., on the other hand, has beenslower to adopt similar reforms.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1139, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The U.S.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1078}, {\"ngram\": \"the other hand\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"beenslower\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1113}, {\"ngram\": \"similar reforms\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1138}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For 100 years in the U.S., we have built streets, neighborhoods and cities around cars, and as a result most people live in auto-dependent neighborhoods, and it's very hard to undo that,\\\" said Nicholas Klein, professor of city and regional planning at Cornell University.\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1413, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1335, \"end\": 1343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_II_of_Russia\", \"score\": 0.9980695410490517, \"rank\": 0.0019341902813860973, \"text\": \"Nicholas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_II_of_Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_II_of_Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1344, \"end\": 1349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Calvin_Klein\", \"score\": 0.9116044811092597, \"rank\": 0.08778529873678623, \"text\": \"Klein\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q3501317\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Calvin_Klein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Calvin_Klein\"}, {\"begin\": 1394, \"end\": 1412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cornell_University\", \"score\": 0.9999999119663737, \"rank\": 8.587756878230022e-08, \"text\": \"Cornell University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cornell_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cornell_University\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"100 years\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1155}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1167}, {\"ngram\": \"streets\", \"from\": 1183, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"neighborhoods\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1205}, {\"ngram\": \"cities\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1216}, {\"ngram\": \"cars\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1228}, {\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1245}, {\"ngram\": \"most people\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1257}, {\"ngram\": \"auto-dependent neighborhoods\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1294}, {\"ngram\": \"professor\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1360}, {\"ngram\": \"city\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1368}, {\"ngram\": \"regional planning\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris' new urban landscape will be on display at a challenging time for Hidalgo, who has faced declining approval ratings and a failed presidential run.\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1415, \"end\": 1420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999708507, \"rank\": 2.9157430667192093e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1487, \"end\": 1494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999847819211202, \"rank\": 1.5218310421687625e-05, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"display\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1460}, {\"ngram\": \"a challenging time\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"declining approval ratings\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1536}, {\"ngram\": \"a failed presidential run\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1566}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still,a 2023 pollshowed a majority of Parisians approve of her environmental reforms.\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1653, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a majority\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1602}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisians\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"her environmental reforms\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1652}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Louise Claustre, a resident of the 12th arrondissement and an avid cyclist, told NBC News she's \\\"100%\\\" in favor of Hidalgo's anti-car policies.\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1655, \"end\": 1661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"score\": 0.9391845869836346, \"rank\": 0.0614519699704211, \"text\": \"Louise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\"}, {\"begin\": 1736, \"end\": 1744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_News\", \"score\": 0.9982272934991115, \"rank\": 0.0017758537505320623, \"text\": \"NBC News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_News\"}, {\"begin\": 1770, \"end\": 1777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999847819211202, \"rank\": 1.5218310421687625e-05, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a resident\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1682}, {\"ngram\": \"the 12th arrondissement\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1709}, {\"ngram\": \"an avid cyclist\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1729}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"100%\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1756}, {\"ngram\": \"favor\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will always be in favor of policies that reduce cars and increase walking and biking,\\\" she said, adding that as a Parisian and the mother of a young child, she thinks the city \\\"will be safer and less polluted if there are fewer cars.\\\"\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 2037, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"favor\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1826}, {\"ngram\": \"policies\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1838}, {\"ngram\": \"cars\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 1855}, {\"ngram\": \"a Parisian\", \